In 2017 I moved to Kansas City with nothing but hopes & dreams and a chance at a new start working for a brand new company called NWL. In a year and a half we did so many incredible things in Missouri & Kansas, in that time I became a backstage correspondent, social media manager, TV host, ring announcer, street team member, producer, wrestler and some jobs i’m sure I’m forgetting. All of this with a very small crew who also were doing a million different things. This past week I joined Chris Gough & Gabe (Ben) Miller on their podcast The Worst Territory in the World to tell some stories from that time. Check out my story to give it a listen 💜

#MartiBelle #DominicanDynamite #NWL

Nuestro primer día del padre sin Papi estar físicamente con nosotros. No ha pasado un día que no lo piense, que no lo extrañe. Leí algo interesante reciente, que cuando un ser querido se va uno no solo se siente el dolor de haberlo perdido, también sientes el dolor de todo lo que ellos no van a poder vivir. Y aveces eso es lo que más me duele. 

Feliz día del padre Papi, espero poder seguir adelante, seguir haciendo cosas para que usted se sienta orgulloso de mi. Gracias por todo el amor y cariño que siempre tuvo para cada uno de nosotros y por la alegría que siempre trajo a nuestras vidas 💜 Que no daría por otro abrazo más.

I’m here to stay 💕

Yesterday was the 14th anniversary of my first match 🥹 I spent a year working as a valet & manager at Johnny Rodz’s school WUW, started training in August 2009, and had my first match November 2009. I’ve had so many moments in my career that I never could have dreamed of, crossed off things I dreamed of as a 7 year old kid watching wrestling with my cousins and met people who have completely changed my life. I still have so many items left to cross my list, so as long as my body says we’re good, I’m gonna keep on kicking. 

Wrestling has opened so many doors for me and I’m going to continue dancing my little self through them 💜
